\N<Segi>Mr. Rozaro.
\N<Rozaro>What's the matter, Ms. Segi?

\N<Segi>Well... I heard that you won the recent match without any
trouble. Congratulations.

\N<Rozaro>Haha, thank you. But it was just a victory against fellow
townspeople. It's not really something to celebrate.
\N<Segi>Right... I suppose so.

\N<Rozaro>What's wrong? You look down. If it's okay with me, I'm
willing to listen to your story.
\N<Segi>It's just that... actually...
op_セギ01a
\N<Rozaro>...I see.

Segi, who sat down next to Rozaro, spoke to him about what
the spectators at the recent military exercise were saying
and her feelings for her husband who was participating in
it.

\N<Segi>The people in town who saw the match were saying it. Indeed,
Mr. Rozaro's strength is exceptional.
\N<Rozaro>...

\N<Segi>I... I'm envious of you, Mr. Rozaro. If only I had the power
to fight like you...

\N<Segi>Then I wouldn't have to burden Lord Yuia alone as I do now.
And it would also mean being able to protect Riia in the
future...

\N<Rozaro>...Ms. Segi, I understand your concern. Indeed, if one does
not acquire the power they wish for themselves, they will
continue to regret and grind their teeth over the same
issues.

\N<Rozaro>I surmise that's exactly what you're going through right
now. As you know, I'm not omnipotent either. There are
nights when I remember my past helplessness and even shed
tears.
\N<Segi>Mr. Rozaro...

\N<Rozaro>That's why I understand your feelings all too well. However,
what's important now is whether Lord Yuia wants you to be
strong for him.

\N<Rozaro>Ms. Segi, you are already strong. As a woman... and as a
mother. Would Yuia seek physical strength from you?

\N<Rozaro>I don't think so. Rather, your desire to be strong might be
seen as a result of your own perceived weaknesses, don't you
think?
\N<Rozaro>Your husband... Yuia isn't that kind of man, is he?
\N<Segi>Maybe... you're right.

\N<Rozaro>That being said... I do understand how you feel. The
military exercise has just begun. It's natural to be
confused by everything.

\N<Rozaro>But that's exactly why... it might not be bad to take a
moment and think things over again, for Riia's sake as well.
\N<Segi>...Yes.
\N<Man>Hey, Rozaro... can I have a moment?

A man's voice suddenly called out from behind Segi and the
others. Looking back, they saw a man with an anxious
expression looking their way.
\N<Rozaro>What do you need?

\N<Man>Actually, I have a match tomorrow. It's my first time
participating in that military exercise...
\N<Rozaro>Is that so? What about it?

\N<Man>So... even though it's last-minute, there's something I want
you to teach me...
\N<Rozaro>I see. But can't you see? I'm busy right now.

\N<Rozaro>Besides... as you said, even if I give you a bit of
guidance, it will be nothing more than a quick fix. In a
battle where lives are at stake, such things won't make much
of a difference.
\N<Man>I know that... but please, somehow...
\N<Rozaro>...

\N<Segi>Mr. Rozaro... I don't mean to be presumptuous, but could you
please consider his request?
\N<Rozaro>However...

\N<Segi>Please don't worry about me. Go ahead, I'll wait here for
you.
\N<Rozaro>...Understood. Then allow me to step away for a moment.
\N<Segi>Yes, take care.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hey, you hear about that guy from the match earlier? His
opponent was a woman and yet he still ended up losing, can
you believe it?

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Yeah, seems so. Honestly, every man in this town is nothing
but a bunch of weaklings, it's pathetic.

\N<Segi>Those soldiers are talking about the training match...
right?

\N<Segi>He lost to a woman... Could it be Ms. Irime they're talking
about...? That means, if you think about it the other way,
Ms. Irime won...

\N<Segi>If that's the case... I'm glad. She was able to win her
match safely...
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Oh?
\N<Segi>...?
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe, nice. This one's a real find.
op_セギ01aaa
\N<Segi>Wha...!?
op_セギ01b

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe, what a fine woman. In this dreary town with its filthy
taverns, all you get is cheap booze and dull women, but this
is a nice change.
\N<Segi>Do you need something from me...?

The Ryuda soldiers unhesitatingly took up positions beside
Segi, letting their leering gazes crawl over her body.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Yeah, we've got business alright. Hey hey, big-breasted
lady, are you alone? If so, why don't you join us for some
fun? Pour us some drinks.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Ahaha, nice. Drinking while gazing at those big breasts of
yours must be really sweet, hehe.

\N<Segi>Please don't speak to me with such filthy words...! And I'm
not alone...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Huh? You look pretty alone to me. Come on, it's fine,
comfort this poor body that's been worn down by daily
duties.
\N<Segi>Stop... please stop this...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe... But seriously, lady, you've got a really nice body
there. Are those breasts real? Let me check them out a bit?

The men began to reach out towards her fair skin as if it
were the most natural thing to do. Segi trembled with
revulsion and raised her voice in protest.
\N<Segi>Please stop... I'll scream!?
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Go ahead, scream. If you think that'll bring help.
\N<Segi>Gah...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>See? You get it now? If you understand, then be a good girl
and have some fun with us?
op_セギ01c
\N<Segi>!?

Ignoring Segi's resistance, the men began to lay their hands
on her clothes. Before their eyes, parts of her white and
ample body were exposed.
\N<Segi>Stop...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe, so these huge tits are real, huh? Lucky us to catch
such a fine woman in a place like this.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Really, really. It's regrettable we haven't laid hands on
such a prize until now.
\N<Segi>Treating people like objects...!

\N<Segi>Listen here...! No matter how much you Ryuda soldiers stay
stationed here and keep watch...! If you keep doing things
like this, winning over the hearts of the people will remain
an unattainable dream...!
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe, is that so. Thanks for the advice.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Well, no need to worry about us. Winning hearts and minds is
a job for those higher up. Us lowly soldiers just take our
pleasures where we can.
\N<Segi>Someone... please...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>It's useless, I told you didn't I? There's no one here who
wants to start trouble with us Ryuda. The people of this
town are all cowards who prefer to avoid conflict, hehe.

\N<Segi>That's not true...! Take back what you said about the
townspeople...!
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe. Even if you defend them, it won't change anything.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>They're cowards for sure. Even now, maybe they're not
thinking of helping you but are looking forward to what's
going to happen next? To your... voluptuous body, huh?

\N<Segi>Please stop saying such irresponsible things...! Not
everyone is a self-centered beast like you...!
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Oh? Shall we put that to the test then?
\N<Segi>Wha...!?
\N<Segi>Stop...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hey hey, it's going to show? Isn't there anyone brave enough
to help this lady out?
\N<The Surrounding Guests>...
\N<Segi>Stop...!
\N<Segi>Please... let go of me...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hehe, you see? The people of this town can't even protect
their own, a bunch of spineless cowards.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Now that you understand, hurry up and move those annoying
hands away and show us everything. Then we'll protect you in
place of these pathetic people, alright?
\N<Rozaro>What are you doing?
\N<Segi>Ro... Rozaro-san...!

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Huh? Who the hell are you? What are we doing, you ask? Can't
you see? We're enjoying ourselves here, don't interfere.

\N<Rozaro>Enjoying yourselves? Hmph, don't make me laugh. It seems
only you lot are having fun.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>What did you say? What are you trying to do? Don't tell me
you're playing the hero to save the girl?
\N<Rozaro>...

\N<Ryuda Soldier>Kukuku, that's rich. Maybe I should give you a taste of pain
then?
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Hm...? Wait a minute. This guy... he's Rozaro...
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Ah? That guy who stood out at the training corps...?
\N<Rozaro>Indeed, I am that Rozaro. So what if I am?
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Grr...!

\N<Rozaro>Scram, lowly soldiers. And never show your hideous faces
before me again.
\N<Ryuda Soldier>Tch... don't get cocky... remember this.

\N<Rozaro>Segi-san, are you alright? I apologize for leaving my seat
and giving them the opportunity...

\N<Segi>No... please don't worry about it. More importantly, I'm
glad you came, Rozaro-san. Thank you very much.
\N<Rozaro>...Yeah.

A

\N<Rozaro>Segi-san, are you alright? I'm sorry, it happened while I
was away from my seat...

\N<Segi>No... please don't worry about it. More importantly, I'm
glad that you came, Rozaro-san. Thank you very much.

\N<Rozaro>...Be careful, Miss Segi. Exercise extreme caution. Among
the monsters roaming the ruins, some possess special self-
defense instincts to protect themselves.

\N<Rozaro>Also... if the soldiers of Ryuda try to blame you for
anything, just say you're a warrior participating in the
training assembly. That's why you're entering the ruins.
\N<Segi>Understood. Thank you for everything.

\N<Rozaro>It's fine... This is all I can do. At the very least, I'm
praying for your safety...

\N<Man>If you don't need anything, please don't talk to me.
Drinking here is the only way I can forget this harsh
reality...
\N<Segi>...Good afternoon, Rozaro-san.
\N<Riia>Master! Good afternoon!

\N<Rozaro>If it isn't Segi-san and Riia. What brings you two to a
place like this?

\N<Segi>We're waiting for my husband's meeting to end. They told us
at the management office that it would take a little more
time.

\N<Rozaro>Ah, I see. So the management office is having that
discussion right now.
\N<Segi>Yes... Um, Rozaro-san, aren't you participating?

\N<Rozaro>Ah. I'm not as wise as your husband... Yuia. At best, I'm a
man whose only talent lies in swinging a weapon, that's the
extent of my battlefield prowess.

\N<Rozaro>What good would an uneducated boar like me do at a meeting?
I'd only serve to needlessly confuse those around me.
\N<Segi>That's not true... You've also been taking care of my son...

\N<Rozaro>Ah, you mean Riia's swordsmanship. Well, it's only basic
instruction, but yeah.

\N<Riia>Master! When is our next training session!? I've gotten
pretty strong!

\N<Rozaro>Hmm... Soon. Until then, make sure you listen well to what
your father and mother say, alright?
\N<Riia>Yeah! It's a promise!
\N<Segi>Thank you so much... I'm really grateful to you, Rozaro-san.
\N<Segi>I can't... be there for everything concerning this child...
\N<Rozaro>...
\N<Segi>And yet, at a time like this... I'm such a terrible mother.

\N<Rozaro>Not at all. If you were a terrible mother, then most mothers
in the world would be terrible.
\N<Segi>Hehe, even if it's flattery, it makes me happy. Thank you.

\N<Rozaro>No, in these unpredictable times, it's better for Riia to
learn how to fight early on. That's how one becomes strong,
just like his father Yuia.

\N<Segi>That's true... It's sad, but perhaps that's the reality of
our situation.

\N<Rozaro>Yuia... your husband is strong. As a warrior, as a person,
and as a man too.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Rozaro>It's unclear how this meeting will turn out. Naturally, that
includes what comes after as well.

\N<Rozaro>But in any case... I'd prefer to avoid any confrontation
with Yuia, no matter how things may unfold.

\N<Rozaro>It might be considered futile, but I'm not giving up on
finding a way to make that happen.
\N<Segi>...Yes.
A

\N<Man>The residents have started fighting each other at the
training sessions, and everyone's becoming more
aggressive... Perhaps it's part of the Ryuda group's aim.

\N<Man>Lately, even in a place like this, Ryuda's soldiers have
started showing up. I just want to drink my booze in
peace...

\N<Man>I don't have the strength to win matches, nor do I have the
power to train myself against monsters in the ruins. Is it
my fate to just die like this...

\N<Man>It's embarrassing to admit, but my wife and I have both
grown cold-hearted towards each other, and we no longer
function as a married couple.

\N<Man>And yet, why must I risk my life for her by participating in
the training soldiers' tournament...
